    "reasoning": "The problem requires finding the probability that some student must pass another to reach an aisle when s = 6 students finish tests in random order. First, p is the portion of the rubber band traversed during the first minute. Initially 4 inches long, the ant walks 1 inch (1/4 of the band), and stretching preserves this fraction, so p = 1/4. Then s = p + 23/4 = 6. For 6 students in a row, the probability that some student must pass another is 1 minus the probability all students can exit without passing. Good permutations (where each student can exit left or right) are 2^(n-1) = 32 for n=6. Total permutations = 720. Thus, probability = 1 - 32/720 = 43/45.",
